 as da ratio.  Me belieb 'eberyting' be read on des boards so me hab used dis me hole life.<br>
<br>
Me questin be, how much shoud da trade off be and why is ratio so important?<br>
<br>
Me trust me warrio bruhda's so me neber question dis.  But me try ter expain it ta a ranja guildie me hang wit lots and not know how ta.  She was tinkin ub sellin her edge of da nightwalker fer a defenders lightblade.  Da ratio on da Edge be better but da lighblade hab more damage.  So me not know why she shud go wit da betta ratio ova da more damage.  Me not find link ta da Lightblade so me not know da exact numba's. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144690" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:yellow;font-family:papyrus;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Oulurok</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shelrabbi>Shelrabbi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/14/02 5:04:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4409.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Offhand ratio/delay?</span><hr size=1> Please, next time you have a question about game mechanics, drop character. Took me 5 minutes to figure out what you were asking <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
People say Ratio &gt; Delay because there is no damage bonus applied to your off hand. So the damage you do with your offhand remains a constant, more or less, based SOLELY on the dam/del of your weapon.<br>
<br>
However there comes a point when this changes and it becomes more important for you to swing your offhand more often then it does to have a superior ration with it. For example, if you have crit disc 6, then the more often you swing your offhand the more often you crit with it. At level 6, it very well may be that your delay &gt; your ratio. If you have a nice procing weapon, say a kreizenns (11/17 100 pt dd) it might be better then a 22/34 or a 25/33 even.<br>
<br>
There are so many intangibles right now that no one knows for sure what delays/ratios/procs/AAs change what weapons to what level of goodness. I recomend picking up a nice parsing program and just test your DPS yourself to determine what weapons to use.<br>
<br>
One fact I can state though: when MTing, it's all about speed. More swings means more hate means you get hit more means other people get hit less. <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>
